- Okay.

271
00:10:44,177 --> 00:10:47,747
[♪♪]

272
00:10:51,785 --> 00:10:52,552
You've never seen so much
complaining in your life.

273
00:10:52,586 --> 00:10:54,721
It's a nightmare,
I'm telling you.

274
00:10:54,754 --> 00:10:55,989
Hello.

275
00:10:57,157 --> 00:11:00,894
Ohh. I'd really hoped we'd seen
the last of "Enema Man".

276
00:11:00,927 --> 00:11:01,895
"Enema Man"?

277
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:03,630
What's...
What's that even mean?

278
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:06,366
[laughs] Well... you'll see.

279
00:11:08,202 --> 00:11:09,769
Um, can I show you guys
something?

280
00:11:09,803 --> 00:11:10,503
<i>Although we were
all making money,</i>

281
00:11:10,537 --> 00:11:12,505
<i>we weren't making enough,</i>

282
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:13,640
<i>and I wanted better
for myself,</i>

283
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:15,508
<i>the girls, and my kids.</i>

284
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:17,611
Okay, so,
I was going over the books...

285
00:11:17,644 --> 00:11:18,411
Who told you to do that?

286
00:11:18,445 --> 00:11:21,615
No one. I was just
trying to help

287
00:11:21,648 --> 00:11:23,483
and thinking about how
to increase profit margins.

288
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,584
Good on you.
Let's hear it.

289
00:11:24,618 --> 00:11:27,554
Okay. So, we do great business
on Saturdays, right?

290
00:11:27,587 --> 00:11:28,655
Between 4:00 and 9:00,

291
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:31,591
we make anywhere between
$800 to $1,500, on average,

292
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:33,026
but we're still
competing against

293
00:11:33,059 --> 00:11:34,194
every other massage parlor
on the street...

294
00:11:34,228 --> 00:11:37,030
- there's six, by the way.
- I'm aware.

295
00:11:37,063 --> 00:11:39,099
But, on Sundays,
only Big Freddie's is open,

296
00:11:39,132 --> 00:11:39,866
and that's from 10:00 to 2:00.

297
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,968
So we could open
from noon to 6:00

298
00:11:42,002 --> 00:11:42,502
and charge a premium.

299
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:44,638
If business is good,

300
00:11:44,671 --> 00:11:47,707
I mean, we could increase
our weekly profits by 30%.

301
00:11:47,741 --> 00:11:48,842
"Our"?

302
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:49,542
Your.

303
00:11:49,576 --> 00:11:50,677
I like it.

304
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:53,013
I don't.

305
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,849
Wait. Why not?

306
00:11:55,882 --> 00:11:58,485
You get greedy,
you get pinched.

307
00:11:58,518 --> 00:12:00,687
It's not greed, it's...
it's expansion.

308
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,789
Don't ask me again.

309
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:06,092
Hmm. I'll talk to her.

310
00:12:06,126 --> 00:12:07,994
Speaking of expansion...

311
00:12:08,028 --> 00:12:10,563
you might want to grab
an extra bottle of bleach.

312
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:12,565
Why?

313
00:12:12,599 --> 00:12:13,466
[Anna] <i>Enema man...</i>

314
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,502
<i>so this was my life.</i>

315
00:12:15,535 --> 00:12:17,170
<i>I was as far away
from the American Dream</i>

316
00:12:17,204 --> 00:12:17,771
<i>as I could get.</i>

317
00:12:17,804 --> 00:12:19,539
[Tina] They're so cute.

318
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:21,775
[both chuckling]

319
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:22,742
<i>Mira.</i>

320
00:12:22,776 --> 00:12:24,010
[Anna] Is that Marjie?

321
00:12:24,044 --> 00:12:25,545
Hey, Marjie!

322
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:27,281
Oh.

323
00:12:27,315 --> 00:12:29,250
Well...

324
00:12:29,283 --> 00:12:31,785
I guess she's too fancy
for us now.

325
00:12:31,818 --> 00:12:33,586
Enema Man
was her breaking point.

326
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,021
I don't get it.

327
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:38,124
There's what I do
at the parlor...

328
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:39,726
$40 to $60 a pop...

329
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,861
then there's what she does now.

330
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:43,964
How much?

331
00:12:43,997 --> 00:12:45,131
Thousand an hour?

332
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:46,633
- What?
- Minimum.

333
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:48,902
Maybe more.
She's "A"-list now.

334
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:50,537
I was making
that kind of cash,

335
00:12:50,570 --> 00:12:52,906
I would leave my Hector
tomorrow.

336
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:54,708
He gets so emotional,
you know?

337
00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:56,743
Maybe I could go
back to school.

338
00:12:56,776 --> 00:12:58,511
Put some savings away
for the kids.

339
00:12:58,545 --> 00:12:59,280
Hmm.

340
00:12:59,313 --> 00:13:02,082
Buy a few
investment properties,

341
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:03,883
like a real boss.

342
00:13:03,917 --> 00:13:05,952
What's going on
in that brain of yours?

343
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:08,255
[Anna chuckles quietly]

344
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:13,626
[singing quietly, indistinct]

345
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:14,961
[buzzer blares]

346
00:13:14,995 --> 00:13:16,963
[blaring]

347
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,535
Hi. Do you have an appointment?

348
00:13:22,569 --> 00:13:24,838
I, uh...

349
00:13:24,871 --> 00:13:26,307
- What's your name?
- Is Tina here?

350
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,641
I actually sent her out
to run a few errands...

351
00:13:28,675 --> 00:13:29,276
[loudly] I know she's here!

352
00:13:29,310 --> 00:13:31,544
I can smell her perfume!

353
00:13:31,578 --> 00:13:34,547
I know she's with someone.

354
00:13:34,581 --> 00:13:35,483
I know what she does.

355
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:39,220
Okay. She is one of
our best masseuses.

356
00:13:39,253 --> 00:13:40,254
Is she with someone now?

357
00:13:40,287 --> 00:13:41,322
I want to see her! And him!

358
00:13:41,355 --> 00:13:43,023
Out here! Right now!

359
00:13:43,056 --> 00:13:44,024
Okay.

360
00:13:44,691 --> 00:13:46,593
Whoa.

361
00:13:46,626 --> 00:13:48,561
Tina!

362
00:13:48,595 --> 00:13:50,697
Tina! Come out here right now!

363
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:51,598
Shame on you.

364
00:13:51,631 --> 00:13:52,532
Give that to me.

365
00:13:55,369 --> 00:13:57,338
What? Shame on me?

366
00:13:57,371 --> 00:13:58,638
Yeah, Tina said you were smart,

367
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:00,774
that you were
a hard-working man.

368
00:14:00,807 --> 00:14:02,309
What the hell is wrong with you?

369
00:14:02,343 --> 00:14:03,511
You have two great kids!

370
00:14:03,543 --> 00:14:05,346
And you want to come into
your wife's place of employment

371
00:14:05,379 --> 00:14:06,813
with a gun

372
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:08,848
and accuse her of doing
something inappropriate?

373
00:14:08,882 --> 00:14:10,351
Are you stupid? Are you?

374
00:14:10,384 --> 00:14:11,584
No.

375
00:14:11,618 --> 00:14:12,585
Are you crazy?

376
00:14:12,619 --> 00:14:13,853
No! I just wasn't...

377
00:14:13,887 --> 00:14:14,721
...Thinking!
Yes, that's right.

378
00:14:14,754 --> 00:14:15,755
You weren't thinking,
but that's okay,

379
00:14:15,789 --> 00:14:16,790
'cause I'm gonna think
for the both of us, okay?

380
00:14:16,823 --> 00:14:21,027
Now, give me the gun
before you ruin your life.

381
00:14:21,061 --> 00:14:22,762
Come on, I don't have
all day, all right?

382
00:14:22,796 --> 00:14:23,830
So give me the gun
before I call the cops

383
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,732
and tell them that
Hector Mendoza's a psychopath

384
00:14:25,765 --> 00:14:27,368
- and he...
- I'm not a psychopath.

385
00:14:27,401 --> 00:14:28,902
Don't make me
count to three, okay?

386
00:14:28,935 --> 00:14:30,136
- [Hector sobbing]
- One...

387
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:32,005
[Hector sobs]

388
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:33,606
Two...

389
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:34,808
[Anna shrieks]

390
00:14:36,743 --> 00:14:38,812
Chill out! Chill out!

391
00:14:39,913 --> 00:14:41,848
Chill! You all right?

392
00:14:43,716 --> 00:14:45,985
[Letty] What the hell
were you thinking?

393
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:46,686
It's not that big of a deal.

394
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,755
What are you talking about?

395
00:14:48,788 --> 00:14:50,757
Calling the cops
is a huge deal!

396
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:51,624
Tina never
should have done that.

397
00:14:51,658 --> 00:14:53,726
She's fired.

398
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,628
Whoa! Can we just think
about this rationally?

399
00:14:55,662 --> 00:14:56,530
There were gunshots.

400
00:14:56,564 --> 00:14:57,864
What the hell
was she supposed to do?

401
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,333
Not call the cops!

402
00:14:59,366 --> 00:15:00,468
Now we're on their radar.

403
00:15:00,501 --> 00:15:04,371
I got a whole department
wanting massages for 25% off.

404
00:15:04,405 --> 00:15:06,840
That's the last thing we need!

405
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:10,311
Why'd you even open the door
in the first place?

406
00:15:10,344 --> 00:15:12,912
I thought he was a customer
and we needed the money.

407
00:15:12,946 --> 00:15:14,747
We always need the money

408
00:15:14,781 --> 00:15:16,149
because you refuse to update

409
00:15:16,182 --> 00:15:17,684
and modernize
your business practices.

410
00:15:17,717 --> 00:15:19,719
Just because you read a book

411
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,788
doesn't mean you know
how to run a business, Anna.

412
00:15:21,821 --> 00:15:22,922
It's common sense. Okay?

413
00:15:22,956 --> 00:15:25,158
If we charged a premium,

414
00:15:25,191 --> 00:15:27,026
we would have
higher-quality clients,

415
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,161
the girls would work less,

416
00:15:28,194 --> 00:15:30,763
and we wouldn't have to hustle
for every single dime.

417
00:15:30,797 --> 00:15:31,731
I mean, Enema Man?

418
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,967
One point Anna.

419
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,736
Look, I've run
the numbers, okay?

420
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,738
Work smarter not harder.

421
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,441
We could do so much
for ourselves,

422
00:15:40,474 --> 00:15:43,810
for the girls,
for everyone,

423
00:15:43,843 --> 00:15:45,879
if we just make a few changes.

424
00:15:45,912 --> 00:15:46,447
I like this.
Two points Anna.

425
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,882
Goodnight, Arthur.

426
00:15:48,915 --> 00:15:50,351
Yep. Goodnight.

427
00:15:50,384 --> 00:15:52,319
Good luck.

428
00:15:56,457 --> 00:15:59,826
So you think
you can do better?

429
00:15:59,859 --> 00:16:01,428
I think
the girls can do better.

430
00:16:01,462 --> 00:16:04,197
And I think you can do better.

431
00:16:11,272 --> 00:16:13,374
I like my place.

432
00:16:13,407 --> 00:16:15,442
[Anna sighs]

433
00:16:15,476 --> 00:16:17,478
I can afford my place.

434
00:16:17,511 --> 00:16:20,713
It's people like you

435
00:16:20,747 --> 00:16:23,250
who think too big
and aim too high

436
00:16:23,284 --> 00:16:24,451
that end up in prison.

437
00:16:24,485 --> 00:16:25,486
Don't fire Tina.

438
00:16:25,519 --> 00:16:26,986
It's already done.

439
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:28,255
Well, then, if she goes,

440
00:16:28,289 --> 00:16:29,923
I go.

441
00:16:32,759 --> 00:16:35,161
Fine.

442
00:16:36,763 --> 00:16:39,366
Fine.

443
00:16:43,537 --> 00:16:45,372
[Anna] <i>I was at rock bottom.</i>

444
00:16:45,406 --> 00:16:47,241
<i>No money, no job,</i>

445
00:16:47,274 --> 00:16:48,841
<i>and was about to be
thrown out on the street</i>

446
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:49,809
<i>with my kids.</i>

447
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,445
So what do we do now?

448
00:16:53,447 --> 00:16:55,181
We could be secretaries.

449
00:16:55,216 --> 00:16:56,816
Yeah.

450
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:58,952
I'd let you come stay with us,

451
00:16:58,985 --> 00:17:00,954
but me and the kids are back
living with my mother.

452
00:17:03,189 --> 00:17:04,425
Look.

453
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:05,925
Letty won't tell you this,

454
00:17:05,959 --> 00:17:06,627
but in the six months
that you worked there,

455
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,962
things have never run smoother...

456
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:10,163
except that last part.

457
00:17:10,196 --> 00:17:12,131
- Really?
- Art said so every day.

458
00:17:14,235 --> 00:17:15,202
Milo! Celeste!

459
00:17:15,236 --> 00:17:16,869
<i>Vamonos.</i>

460
00:17:16,903 --> 00:17:19,406
Why don't you open
your own business?

461
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,441
Seriously?

462
00:17:20,474 --> 00:17:22,376
Why not?

463
00:17:22,409 --> 00:17:22,809
I'd come work for you.

464
00:17:26,513 --> 00:17:28,081
Think about it.

465
00:17:30,551 --> 00:17:32,219
See you around.

466
00:17:32,253 --> 00:17:33,287
Yeah.

467
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,288
<i>Ándale, mijitos.</i>

468
00:17:34,321 --> 00:17:35,955
Let's go.

469
00:17:35,989 --> 00:17:36,624
[Anna]
<i>And that's when I decided</i>

470
00:17:36,657 --> 00:17:38,492
<i>I had to take a leap.</i>

471
00:17:38,525 --> 00:17:39,393
<i>I had nothing to lose.</i>

472
00:17:40,494 --> 00:17:42,128
[dialing phone]

473
00:17:43,029 --> 00:17:44,565
<i>[line ringing]</i>

474
00:17:44,598 --> 00:17:47,934
Hey, Art? It's me.

475
00:17:47,967 --> 00:17:49,536
I have a crazy idea.

476
00:17:50,604 --> 00:17:52,573
Well, kids.

477
00:17:52,606 --> 00:17:55,309
What do you think?

478
00:17:55,342 --> 00:17:56,310
It's gross.

479
00:17:56,343 --> 00:17:57,411
Smells like poop.

480
00:17:57,444 --> 00:17:59,912
No, John Christopher.
This smells like potential.

481
00:17:59,946 --> 00:18:02,181
I see it.

482
00:18:02,216 --> 00:18:04,150
Oh, by the way, you're it.

483
00:18:05,452 --> 00:18:07,920
[Anna] <i>I started my business
with a $5,000 loan from Arthur</i>

484
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:09,456
<i>and what I'd learned
from my cousin,</i>

485
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:10,457
<i>but I wasn't
going to have my girls</i>

486
00:18:10,491 --> 00:18:12,459
<i>service nobodies
for pennies a pop.</i>

487
00:18:12,493 --> 00:18:15,462
<i>They were going to get paid
what they were worth.</i>

488
00:18:15,496 --> 00:18:18,197
<i>We were going to be the ones
in control.</i>

489
00:18:18,232 --> 00:18:19,566
<i>We were going to be exclusive.</i>

490
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:22,935
[♪♪]

491
00:18:29,075 --> 00:18:30,043
[♪♪]

492
00:18:30,076 --> 00:18:31,378
[knocking]

493
00:18:31,412 --> 00:18:33,380
Anna Christine,
ladies and gentlemen!

494
00:18:33,414 --> 00:18:34,615
[Anna]
<i>If I was going to be the best,</i>

495
00:18:34,648 --> 00:18:35,982
<i>I had to hire the best.</i>

496
00:18:36,015 --> 00:18:37,384
Look at you!

497
00:18:37,418 --> 00:18:37,817
We're gonna do it.

498
00:18:40,554 --> 00:18:41,722
Do you have boyfriends?

499
00:18:41,755 --> 00:18:43,290
<i>Tina told her friends,
who told their friends,</i>

500
00:18:43,324 --> 00:18:44,658
<i>and so on.</i>

501
00:18:44,692 --> 00:18:46,627
<i>The girls knew me, liked me,
and wanted to work for me.</i>

502
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:48,595
<i>I made it a point to interview
every last one of them.</i>

503
00:18:48,629 --> 00:18:50,597
Do you do drugs?

504
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:53,634
<i>First rule. No drugs.</i>

505
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:54,934
<i>But I was tough.</i>

506
00:18:58,405 --> 00:19:01,342
[♪♪]

507
00:19:03,243 --> 00:19:05,346
Do you drink? Smoke? Party?

508
00:19:05,379 --> 00:19:05,813
Never.

509
00:19:05,845 --> 00:19:07,980
This is a temple.

510
00:19:08,014 --> 00:19:11,585
Husband?
Boyfriend? Lover?

511
00:19:11,618 --> 00:19:12,586
No man alive that lucky.

512
00:19:12,619 --> 00:19:13,320
[Anna] <i>Second rule?
No boyfriends.</i>

513
00:19:13,354 --> 00:19:16,490
- How tall are you?
- I'm 6'1".

514
00:19:16,523 --> 00:19:18,091
70% legs

515
00:19:18,124 --> 00:19:20,927
and the rest
is boobs and attitude.

516
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:21,861
She's great.

517
00:19:24,931 --> 00:19:27,200
Victoria?

518
00:19:27,234 --> 00:19:28,268
Oh...

519
00:19:31,137 --> 00:19:33,440
Vicky. A "Victoria"
would have nicer shoes.

520
00:19:33,474 --> 00:19:35,174
Thank you.

521
00:19:35,209 --> 00:19:35,843
[Anna] <i>Vicky Grant.</i>

522
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:38,479
<i>I liked her right away.</i>

523
00:19:38,512 --> 00:19:40,146
So tell me about you.

524
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,516
What do I need to know?

525
00:19:42,549 --> 00:19:45,118
Well, I left home when I was 15
for reasons I won't get into,

526
00:19:45,151 --> 00:19:46,953
but you know who JR is?

527
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:47,821
I'm gonna be like him,

528
00:19:47,855 --> 00:19:49,989
but, like,
the female version of him.

529
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,558
I believe in playing for keeps

530
00:19:51,592 --> 00:19:53,293
and the best revenge
is living well.

531
00:19:53,327 --> 00:19:55,128
But just because I'm a runaway
doesn't mean I'm stupid.

532
00:19:55,161 --> 00:19:56,663
I'm putting myself
